{
  "texts": [
    "T n and T e represent the natural language attributes of the corresponding nodes and edges in the graph.",
    "Textual Subgraphs are subgraph structures in a textual graph, e.g., G with finite node set V and edge set E, we have its subgraph set",
    ", where P(V) and P(E) represent the power set of V and E, respectively.",
    "Graph Retrieval Augmented Generation (GRAG) aims to integrate graph context into both the retrieval and generation phases, improving the relevance of generated content to the knowledge embedded within the textual graph.",
    "Given a specific query q over a textual graph G, there exists an optimal textual subgraph ĝ ∈ S(G) that leads the LLM to generate answers that align with expectations, where S(G) denotes the set of all subgraphs of G. The objective of GRAG is to retrieve the optimal subgraph ĝ and incorporate its information into an LLM θ parameterized by θ to enhance the generation process."
  ]
}